1
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:41,180
=In Marriage and Beyond=

2
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,180
=Episode 5=

3
00:02:04,980 --> 00:02:05,860
It's almost time.

4
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:07,990
Let's see if he's on time today.

5
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:23,980
Stop pretending to work.

6
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,700
Today's workload isn't that heavy.

7
00:02:26,540 --> 00:02:27,460
Leave early

8
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:29,910
before you get stuck in traffic.

9
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:36,060
Let's go!

10
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:43,300
Don't you guys think

11
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,980
our new director is pretty funny?

12
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,360
He's more punctual about leaving work

13
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:50,100
than he is about coming in.

14
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:52,380
Qian, do you really love
working overtime that much?

15
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,700
Do you even have a life outside of work?

16
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:58,020
Come on,

17
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:02,780
let me tell you what "life" really is.

18
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:04,700
Take "life" as living

19
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:06,060
and "life" as alive.

20
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:09,020
When the two of you are separate,
it's super chill.

21
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:12,020
But one day,

22
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,500
when you're combined,

23
00:03:14,180 --> 00:03:16,140
you'll understand what life truly is.

24
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:20,300
That kind of makes sense.

25
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,820
Who are you trying to match up, though?

26
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:27,780
So boring.

27
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:29,420
See you tomorrow.

28
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:30,940
See you.

29
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:33,140
Wait for me!

30
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:44,410
Why are you just sitting there?

31
00:03:44,410 --> 00:03:45,540
Grab a drink, have a drink!

32
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:47,380
- Let's all drink together!
- Right?

33
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:48,620
It's been years. Come on!

34
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:51,420
Hey, what's this?

35
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:52,860
What?

36
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:55,040
I've already had one, aren't you
going to clink glasses with me?

37
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:56,340
- Hi! Long time no see.
- Long time no see.

38
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:57,860
What, no invite for me?

39
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:58,820
Hu,

40
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,500
if I remember correctly,

41
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,860
your wife works
for some foreign company now, right?

42
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,340
Nonsense.

43
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:07,660
Hu's wife is a public interest lawyer.

44
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:11,180
No, wasn't she

45
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:12,700
Hu's boss before?

46
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:15,180
She switched careers to become a lawyer?

47
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,660
That's my ex-wife.

48
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:18,900
That was ages ago.

49
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:21,180
- Oh, I didn't know.
- Let's drink.

50
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,780
Can't keep it all straight.

51
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:24,140
Come on.

52
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:28,100
You did that on purpose, didn't you?

53
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,100
Do you know where he got
his first fortune?

54
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:31,940
Where?

55
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:35,340
Wasn't it from
divorcing his wealthy ex-wife?

56
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:37,460
And now he's here pretending
to be some start-up elite.

57
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:38,420
Well,

58
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:41,220
now he's rich.

59
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,180
Right?

60
00:04:42,580 --> 00:04:44,100
It's so easy for him to just trade up

61
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:45,420
and marry some do-gooder lawyer.

62
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:47,020
What's he trying to balance out?

63
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:50,330
I'm not putting up with him.

64
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:52,340
Remember back in college?

65
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:53,740
He even stole our stuff.

66
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:55,140
Stop making stuff up.

67
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:56,450
He didn't steal from you.

68
00:04:56,450 --> 00:04:58,060
You remember it wrong.

69
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,180
I remember it wrong?

70
00:05:05,230 --> 00:05:06,740
- Come on, cheers!
- Long time no see.

71
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:08,500
Let's drink!

72
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,300
Come on, cheers.

73
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,300
Sorry everyone,

74
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,380
I'm late.

75
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:14,260
Xuanxuan!

76
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:17,300
- Xuanxuan!
- Xuanxuan!

77
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,540
You finally made it!

78
00:05:19,580 --> 00:05:21,260
Alright, let's make room
for the school belle,

79
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:22,220
shall we?

80
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,140
- Go back to your seat.
- I do.

81
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:25,740
- Come on.
- I do.

82
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,420
Still pretending?

83
00:05:28,420 --> 00:05:30,260
- Your goddess is here.
- Xuanxuan.

84
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:31,420
It's been ages.

85
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:32,580
It really has.

86
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,030
You've changed so much,

87
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:36,460
I almost didn't recognize you.

88
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:37,940
You haven't changed a bit.

89
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:39,140
Still the same as always.

90
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:41,100
Can you not butt in?

91
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,460
Xuanxuan,

92
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,340
let me introduce properly.

93
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:45,300
This is Hu...

94
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,540
Wait,

95
00:05:46,550 --> 00:05:47,740
we can't call him Hu anymore.

96
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,100
He's now Mr. Hu.

97
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:49,940
Mr. Hu.

98
00:05:50,780 --> 00:05:53,780
CEO of a soon-to-be-listed company.

99
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:55,980
He's super busy these days.

100
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:58,900
If it weren't for

101
00:05:58,980 --> 00:06:00,220
your visit back home,

102
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:02,620
we probably wouldn't
have had the chance to see him.

103
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,180
Does anyone here still remember

104
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:05,590
back in school,

105
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:08,080
Mr. Hu wrote

106
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:09,820
something

107
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:10,900
to Xuanxuan.

108
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,940
- A love letter.
- Love letter.

109
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:13,780
Right!

110
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:16,380
There was no love letter!

111
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:18,940
Stop picking on me, seriously.

112
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:19,820
No love letter.

113
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,220
Why can't I remember this at all?

114
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:22,540
They're both denying it,

115
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:25,020
- but I'm sure there was one.
- Xuanxuan.

116
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:26,820
I have to say,

117
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:28,340
anyone can forget about it,

118
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:30,460
yet you can't have forgotten that.

119
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,620
You broke Mr. Hu's heart.

120
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:35,060
Don't make stuff up.

121
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:36,260
Then again,

122
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:38,180
Xuanxuan was so beautiful back then.

123
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:39,940
She must have received
loads of love letters.

124
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:42,420
It's normal if she doesn't remember.

125
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,380
But,

126
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:44,740
Hu

127
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,060
only wrote a love letter

128
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:49,100
to one person in his entire life,

129
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:50,100
right?

130
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:51,070
Hu, is that true?

131
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:54,980
I think he's underestimating me.

132
00:06:56,130 --> 00:06:57,110
Hu,

133
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,340
that's an interesting comment.

134
00:06:58,340 --> 00:06:59,930
- Is that how it is?
- Good for you.

135
00:06:59,930 --> 00:07:01,580
Hu says he doesn't remember.

136
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,660
Should I spill the beans?

137
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:05,080
- Go ahead.
- Sure.

138
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:07,180
Alright, I'll skip

139
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:08,700
the steamy details.

140
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:11,420
Who told you to skip that part?

141
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,500
Have you seen my watch?

142
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:18,660
Where's my watch? Move!

143
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:20,100
- What are you doing?
- Searching your place.

144
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:22,220
What are you doing? Stop.

145
00:07:22,420 --> 00:07:23,700
Why are you searching my stuff?

146
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:24,940
Why are you suspecting me?

147
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:26,740
I am suspecting you.

148
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:27,580
So what?

149
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:31,210
You're always in the dorm reading.

150
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,260
If it wasn't you, who else could it be?

151
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:34,220
I'm telling you,

152
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,310
give my watch back now,

153
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:38,220
or I swear I'll beat you up!

154
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:50,460
Let's go eat.

155
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:54,140
Did you see the love letter
he wrote to Xuanxuan?

156
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:56,220
Talk about a toad lusting after a swan.

157
00:07:56,580 --> 00:08:00,420
Like the campus belle would ever
look at a bookworm like him.

158
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,080
You're overacting.

159
00:08:02,140 --> 00:08:03,200
Mind your own business.

160
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:04,990
How about this,

161
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,260
- later...
- Yeah.

162
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:07,100
Guys.

163
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,180
Mr. Hu has prepared

164
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:11,140
some small gifts for everyone.

165
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,480
Let me hand them out.

166
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:14,590
Hu.

167
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:15,900
- Is this appropriate?
- Come on.

168
00:08:16,020 --> 00:08:17,220
It's just some promotional items

169
00:08:17,340 --> 00:08:19,340
from a business project
my company is working on.

170
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:21,980
Just take it for fun.

171
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,380
Please take it.

172
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:24,940
- Okay.
- Thank you.

173
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:25,930
Here.

174
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:26,710
- Let me see.
- You're so kind.

175
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:27,700
Look, look.

176
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:29,980
- Take it.
- It's too kind.

177
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:30,940
Yeah.

178
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:31,980
Hu.

179
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,180
- Sorry.
- Let's toast to Hu.

180
00:08:34,340 --> 00:08:35,180
That's it.

181
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,620
I've got one at home.

182
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:38,780
Sorry.

183
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:41,980
The market price for this
is 7,000 to 8,000 yuan!

184
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:42,960
- More like 8,000 plus!
- Come on.

185
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,300
Check it out. Am I right?

186
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,140
Yeah.

187
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:47,460
This is way too generous.

188
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,940
- By the way,
- Right?

189
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,420
about your son's school,

190
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:52,460
I've already spoken to the principal.

191
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,660
Next week, you can take your son

192
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,500
to register.

193
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:57,650
This...

194
00:08:58,020 --> 00:08:59,340
I have to come

195
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:00,660
thank you personally,

196
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:03,060
Hu.

197
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:05,180
I've been worrying about this

198
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,780
for ages.

199
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:08,660
I can't thank you enough.

200
00:09:08,780 --> 00:09:10,370
- No need. It was nothing.
- Come on.

201
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:12,860
Mr. Hu,

202
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,220
my company just developed a new app.

203
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:16,580
- We'll talk about it.
- My financing...

204
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,060
- Hu. Hu.
- Don't worry.

205
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:19,620
- I'll keep all your matters in mind.
- Come on.

206
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:20,820
What are you doing?

207
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,380
Let's toast to Mr. Hu!

208
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:24,260
Cheers.

209
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:25,570
We're all old classmates.

210
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,100
Cheers.

211
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:31,300
We're classmates.

212
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,280
- Hu Cheng.
- We must not be estranged.

213
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,580
Let me add you on WeChat.

214
00:09:34,930 --> 00:09:37,210
- Sure.
- Let's help each other out, right?

215
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:38,980
Okay.

216
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:41,620
You two should add each other too.

217
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,740
We should meet up more often, Hu.

218
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:43,580
- Absolutely.
- Yeah.

219
00:09:43,660 --> 00:09:45,460
Thanks for everything.

220
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:46,660
You're welcome.

221
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,980
Well, wait until the weekends.

222
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:49,180
- I'll be free.
- Okay.

223
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:50,820
Don't worry.

224
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,940
Just call me by then.

225
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:54,140
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

226
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,140
Bye-bye.

227
00:09:56,140 --> 00:09:57,420
Hold him.

228
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,090
What's wrong?

229
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,820
Hu Cheng, what's wrong?

230
00:10:03,820 --> 00:10:05,170
Why didn't you approve
my WeChat request?

231
00:10:05,190 --> 00:10:06,020
Bad signal?

232
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,060
Why are you here?

233
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:29,980
Come in.

234
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:09,020
What's up?

235
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,180
Nothing.

236
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:11,900
I just wanted to check on you.

237
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:13,860
Did the gathering upset you?

238
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:23,500
It's better not to go.

239
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:29,500
Whatever happens,

240
00:11:30,580 --> 00:11:31,860
I'm always here for you.

241
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:42,260
I know.

242
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,900
You'll always stay by my side.

243
00:12:12,620 --> 00:12:14,010
Did I wake you up?

244
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:17,980
Did the gathering go well?

245
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,060
It went great.

246
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:20,260
Very great.

247
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:23,940
We had such a good time,

248
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:26,020
and even lost track of time.

249
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:29,380
Didn't expect it to go so late.

250
00:12:30,060 --> 00:12:31,590
Still up this late?

251
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,510
You've got time to

252
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,480
listen to this music.

253
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:43,680
It's just that

254
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,820
whenever I see this group of guys,

255
00:12:47,460 --> 00:12:48,620
it reminds me

256
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:50,660
of the happy,

257
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,180
carefree days in college.

258
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,220
What are you doing?

259
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:55,500
- Searching your place.
- Stop.

260
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,560
Why are you searching my stuff?

261
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:57,580
What are you suspecting me?

262
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:58,660
I am suspecting you.

263
00:12:58,660 --> 00:12:59,500
So what?

264
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,700
You're always in the dorm reading.

265
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:04,740
If it wasn't you, who else could it be?

266
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:07,070
We don't stay in touch much,

267
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:09,060
but

268
00:13:10,740 --> 00:13:13,460
they're a group of
genuinely close friends.

269
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,300
Mr. Hu,

270
00:13:14,380 --> 00:13:16,020
didn't you write

271
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:16,940
something to Xuanxuan?

272
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:18,680
- A love letter.
- Love letter.

273
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:20,820
Exactly! Hu was so determined
to win you over.

274
00:13:20,820 --> 00:13:22,940
Every weekend, he'd go learn piano,

275
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:24,700
while the rest of us
hit the internet cafe for gaming.

276
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:27,060
- I can vouch for that.
- He worked so hard,

277
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:28,120
sacrificing everything for it.

278
00:13:28,130 --> 00:13:29,660
The most amazing thing is,

279
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:32,180
after all these years,

280
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:34,900
they haven't changed a bit.

281
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:37,300
No pretentiousness,

282
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:38,780
no ulterior motives,

283
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:41,020
just pure,

